lead_paragraph: Appeals judges at a special U.N.-backed tribunal on the assassination of former Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri have overturned the conviction of the manager of a local TV station in Beirut who was found guilty last year of not removing from the station's website information about confidential witnesses in the long-running probe.

headline.main: Court Overturns Lebanese TV Manager's Contempt Conviction
headline.print_headline: Court Overturns Lebanese TV Manager's Contempt Conviction
